<p>Kho Gaye Hum Kahan is a gutsy take on imperfect human relationships in the new age of social media. The film is a fusion of fine writing and mature storytelling. Late teens, and those in their 20s and 30s will find the content very relatable and real. It is a recommended watch and deserves to be binged as we call in the new year.</p>

