]]></description><link>https://www.pinkvilla.com/entertainment/reviews/akelli-movie-review-nushrratt-bharucchas-survival-thriller-is-spine-chilling-and-gut-wrenching-1237662</link><guid  isPermaLink="false">pinkvilla-1237662</guid><pubDate>Wed, 23 Aug 2023 04:35:01 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title><![CDATA[Ahsoka episode 1 &amp; 2 review: Rosario Dawson sets stage for the visual spectacle; new villain terrifies in Star Wars spin-off]]></title><description><![CDATA[<img src="https://www.pinkvilla.com/images/2023-08/175442628_image-1280x720-12-1.jpg"></img><h2 id="66e805ddf1626"><strong>What Doesn&#39;t Work?&nbsp;</strong></h2>

<p>While many aspects of the show are to be marveled over, there are some parts that fall flat. For a D+ production, the series will leave audiences impressed, but word of caution for anyone going into it thinking the visuals will match up to Andor, it won&#39;t. Even though the plot is rich in its lore, if can prove to be a big no-no for casual fans, who are not that well versed with the universe as of yet.&nbsp;</p>

